{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"First place I'd like to take you"},{"time":2000,"text":"is what many believe will be the world's deepest natural abyss."},{"time":6000,"text":"And I say believe because this process is still ongoing."},{"time":9000,"text":"Right now there are major expeditions being planned for next year"},{"time":13000,"text":"that I'll talk a little bit about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15000,"text":"One of the things that's changed here,"},{"time":17000,"text":"in the last 150 years since Jules Verne"},{"time":20000,"text":"had great science-fiction concepts of what the underworld was like,"},{"time":23000,"text":"is that technology has enabled us to go to these places"},{"time":27000,"text":"that were previously completely unknown and speculated about."},{"time":31000,"text":"We can now descend thousands of meters into the Earth with relative impunity."},{"time":36000,"text":"Along the way we've discovered fantastic abysses and chambers so large"},{"time":42000,"text":"that you can see for hundreds of meters"},{"time":44000,"text":"without a break in the line of sight."},{"time":47000,"text":"When you go on a thing like this, we can usually be in the field"},{"time":49000,"text":"for anywhere from two to four months,"},{"time":51000,"text":"with a team as small as 20 or 30, to as big as 150."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"And a lot of people ask me, you know,"},{"time":60000,"text":"what kind of people do you get for a project like this?"},{"time":62000,"text":"While our selection process"},{"time":65000,"text":"is not as rigorous as NASA, it's nonetheless thorough."},{"time":68000,"text":"We're looking for competence, discipline, endurance, and strength."},{"time":73000,"text":"In case you're wondering, this is our strength test."},{"time":75000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":77000,"text":"But we also value esprit de corps"},{"time":81000,"text":"and the ability to diplomatically resolve inter-personal conflict"},{"time":85000,"text":"while under great stress in remote locations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"We have already gone far beyond the limits of human endurance."},{"time":93000,"text":"From the entrance, this is nothing like a commercial cave."},{"time":97000,"text":"You're looking at Camp Two in a place called J2, not K2, but J2."},{"time":101000,"text":"We're roughly two days from the entrance at that point."},{"time":105000,"text":"And it's kind of like a high altitude mountaineering trip in reverse,"},{"time":109000,"text":"except that you're now running a string of these things down."},{"time":111000,"text":"The idea is to try to provide some measure of physical comfort"},{"time":115000,"text":"while you're down there, otherwise in damp, moist, cold conditions in utterly dark places."},{"time":121000,"text":"I should mention that everything you're seeing here, by the way,"},{"time":124000,"text":"is artificially illuminated at great effort."},{"time":127000,"text":"Otherwise it is completely dark in these places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129000,"text":"The deeper you go, the more you run into a conflict with water."},{"time":134000,"text":"It's basically like a tree collecting water coming down."},{"time":138000,"text":"And eventually you get to places where it is formidable and dangerous"},{"time":142000,"text":"and unfortunately slides just don't do justice."},{"time":145000,"text":"So I've got a very brief clip here that was taken in the late 1980s."},{"time":150000,"text":"So descend into Huautla Plateau in Mexico."},{"time":153000,"text":"(Video)"},{"time":157000,"text":"Now I have to tell you that the techniques being shown here"},{"time":160000,"text":"are obsolete and dangerous."},{"time":162000,"text":"We would not do this today unless we were doing it for film."},{"time":166000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"Along that same line, I have to tell you"},{"time":172000,"text":"that with the spate of Hollywood movies that came out last year,"},{"time":175000,"text":"we have never seen monsters underground --"},{"time":179000,"text":"at least the kind that eat you."},{"time":181000,"text":"If there is a monster underground,"},{"time":185000,"text":"it is the crushing psychological remoteness"},{"time":188000,"text":"that begins to hit every member of the team"},{"time":190000,"text":"once you cross about three days inbound from the nearest entrance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195000,"text":"Next year I'll be leading an international team to J2."},{"time":199000,"text":"We're going to be shooting from minus 2,600 meters --"},{"time":201000,"text":"that's a little over 8,600 feet down --"},{"time":204000,"text":"at 30 kilometers from the entrance."},{"time":206000,"text":"The lead crews will be underground for pushing 30 days straight."},{"time":210000,"text":"I don't think there's been a mission like that in a long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"Eventually, if you keep going down in these things,"},{"time":215000,"text":"probability says that you're going to run into a place like this."},{"time":218000,"text":"It's a place where there's a fold in the geologic stratum"},{"time":222000,"text":"that collects water and fills to the roof."},{"time":224000,"text":"And when you used to find these things,"},{"time":227000,"text":"they would put a label on a map that said terminal siphon."},{"time":230000,"text":"Now I remember that term really well for two reasons."},{"time":232000,"text":"Number one, it's the name of my rock band, and second,"},{"time":235000,"text":"is because the confrontation of these things"},{"time":238000,"text":"forced me to become an inventor."},{"time":240000,"text":"And we've since gone on to develop"},{"time":243000,"text":"many generations of gadgets for exploring places like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246000,"text":"This is some life-support equipment closed-cycle."},{"time":249000,"text":"And you can use that now to go for many kilometers horizontally"},{"time":252000,"text":"underwater and to depths of 200 meters straight down underwater."},{"time":256000,"text":"When you do this kind of stuff it's like doing EVA."},{"time":259000,"text":"It's like doing extra-vehicular activity in space,"},{"time":262000,"text":"but at much greater distances, and at much greater physical peril."},{"time":266000,"text":"So it makes you think about how to design your equipment"},{"time":268000,"text":"for long range, away from a safe haven."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271000,"text":"Here's a clip from a National Geographic movie"},{"time":273000,"text":"that came out in 1999."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275000,"text":"(Video) Narrator: Exploration is a physical process"},{"time":277000,"text":"of putting your foot in places where humans have never stepped before."},{"time":281000,"text":"This is where the last little nugget of totally unknown territory remains on this planet."},{"time":286000,"text":"To experience it is a privilege."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293000,"text":"Bill Stone: That was taken in Wakulla Springs, Florida."},{"time":297000,"text":"Couple of things to note about that movie. Every piece of equipment"},{"time":301000,"text":"that you saw in there did not exist before 1999."},{"time":303000,"text":"It was developed within a two-year period and used on actual exploratory projects."},{"time":308000,"text":"This gadget you see right here was called the digital wall mapper,"},{"time":311000,"text":"and it produced the first three-dimensional map anybody has ever done"},{"time":315000,"text":"of a cave, and it happened to be underwater in Wakulla Springs."},{"time":318000,"text":"It was that gadget that serendipitously opened a door"},{"time":322000,"text":"to another unexplored world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"This is Europa."},{"time":327000,"text":"Carolyn Porco mentioned another one called Enceladus the other day."},{"time":331000,"text":"This is one of the places where planetary scientists"},{"time":334000,"text":"believe there is a highest probability of the detection"},{"time":336000,"text":"of the first life off earth in the ocean that exists below there."},{"time":340000,"text":"For those who have never seen this story,"},{"time":342000,"text":"Jim Cameron produced a really wonderful IMAX movie"},{"time":345000,"text":"couple of years ago, called \"Aliens of the Deep.\""},{"time":347000,"text":"There was a brief clip --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"(Video) Narrator: A mission to explore under the ice of Europa"},{"time":353000,"text":"would be the ultimate robotic challenge."},{"time":359000,"text":"Europa is so far away that even at the speed of light,"},{"time":365000,"text":"it would take more than an hour for the command just to reach the vehicle."},{"time":369000,"text":"It has to be smart enough to avoid terrain hazards"},{"time":372000,"text":"and to find a good landing site on the ice."},{"time":384000,"text":"Now we have to get through the ice."},{"time":387000,"text":"You need a melt probe."},{"time":389000,"text":"It's basically a nuclear-heated torpedo."},{"time":402000,"text":"The ice could be anywhere from three to 16 miles deep."},{"time":406000,"text":"Week after week, the melt probe will sink of its own weight"},{"time":409000,"text":"through the ancient ice, until finally --"},{"time":418000,"text":"Now, what are you going to do when you reach the surface of that ocean?"},{"time":424000,"text":"You need an AUV, an autonomous underwater vehicle."},{"time":429000,"text":"It needs to be one smart puppy, able to navigate"},{"time":431000,"text":"and make decisions on its own in an alien ocean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436000,"text":"BS: What Jim didn't know when he released that movie"},{"time":438000,"text":"was that six months earlier NASA had funded a team I assembled"},{"time":443000,"text":"to develop a prototype for the Europa AUV."},{"time":446000,"text":"I mean, I cut through three years of engineering meetings, design"},{"time":451000,"text":"and system integration, and introduced DEPTHX --"},{"time":454000,"text":"Deep Phreatic Thermal Explorer."},{"time":456000,"text":"And as the movie says, this is one smart puppy."},{"time":459000,"text":"It's got 96 sensors, 36 onboard computers,"},{"time":464000,"text":"100,000 lines of behavioral autonomy code,"},{"time":467000,"text":"packs more than 10 kilos of TNT in electrical onboard equivalent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472000,"text":"This is the target site,"},{"time":474000,"text":"the world's deepest hydrothermal spring at Cenote Zacaton in northern Mexico."},{"time":479000,"text":"It's been explored to a depth of 292 meters"},{"time":482000,"text":"and beyond that nobody knows anything."},{"time":485000,"text":"This is part of DEPTHX's mission."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"There are two primary targets we're doing here."},{"time":489000,"text":"One is, how do you do science autonomy underground?"},{"time":491000,"text":"How do you take a robot and turn it into a field microbiologist?"},{"time":495000,"text":"There are more stages involved here"},{"time":497000,"text":"than I've got time to tell you about, but basically we drive"},{"time":499000,"text":"through the space, we populate it with environmental variables --"},{"time":503000,"text":"sulphide, halide, things like that."},{"time":505000,"text":"We calculate gradient surfaces, and drive the bot over to a wall"},{"time":508000,"text":"where there's a high probability of life."},{"time":510000,"text":"We move along the wall, in what's called proximity operations,"},{"time":512000,"text":"looking for changes in color."},{"time":514000,"text":"If we see something that looks interesting, we pull it into a microscope."},{"time":517000,"text":"If it passes the microscopic test, we go for a collection."},{"time":521000,"text":"We either draw in a liquid sample,"},{"time":523000,"text":"or we can actually take a solid core from the wall."},{"time":526000,"text":"No hands at the wheel."},{"time":527000,"text":"This is all behavioral autonomy here"},{"time":529000,"text":"that's being conducted by the robot on its own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"The real hat trick for this vehicle, though,"},{"time":534000,"text":"is a disruptive new navigation system we've developed,"},{"time":537000,"text":"known as 3D SLAM, for simultaneous localization and mapping."},{"time":541000,"text":"DEPTHX is an all-seeing eyeball."},{"time":543000,"text":"Its sensor beams look both forward and backward at the same time,"},{"time":547000,"text":"allowing it to do new exploration"},{"time":550000,"text":"while it's still achieving geometric sensor-lock"},{"time":552000,"text":"on what it's gone through already."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553000,"text":"What I'm going to show you next"},{"time":556000,"text":"is the first fully autonomous robotic exploration underground"},{"time":560000,"text":"that's ever been done."},{"time":611000,"text":"This May, we're going to go from minus 1,000 meters in Zacaton,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and if we're very lucky, DEPTHX will bring back the first"},{"time":617000,"text":"robotically-discovered division of bacteria."},{"time":620000,"text":"The next step after that is to test it in Antartica and then,"},{"time":623000,"text":"if the funding continues and NASA has the resolution to go,"},{"time":626000,"text":"we could potentially launch by 2016, and by 2019"},{"time":630000,"text":"we may have the first evidence of life off this planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634000,"text":"What then of manned space exploration?"},{"time":639000,"text":"The government recently announced plans to return to the moon by 2024."},{"time":643000,"text":"The successful conclusion of that mission will result"},{"time":646000,"text":"in infrequent visitation of the moon by a small number"},{"time":650000,"text":"of government scientists and pilots."},{"time":652000,"text":"It will leave us no further along in the general expansion"},{"time":656000,"text":"of humanity into space than we were 50 years ago."},{"time":659000,"text":"Something fundamental has to change"},{"time":661000,"text":"if we are to see common access to space in our lifetime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"What I'm going to show you next are a couple of controversial ideas."},{"time":668000,"text":"And I hope you'll bear with me and have some faith"},{"time":670000,"text":"that there's credibility behind what we're going to say here."},{"time":674000,"text":"There are three underpinnings of working in space privately."},{"time":681000,"text":"One of them is the requirement"},{"time":683000,"text":"for economical earth-to-space transport."},{"time":686000,"text":"The Bert Rutans and Richard Bransons of this world"},{"time":689000,"text":"have got this in their sights and I salute them."},{"time":691000,"text":"Go, go, go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693000,"text":"The next thing we need are places to stay on orbit."},{"time":696000,"text":"Orbital hotels to start with, but workshops for the rest of us later on."},{"time":699000,"text":"The final missing piece, the real paradigm-buster, is this:"},{"time":705000,"text":"a gas station on orbit."},{"time":708000,"text":"It's not going to look like that."},{"time":710000,"text":"If it existed, it would change all future spacecraft design and space mission planning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716000,"text":"Now, to give you a chance to understand"},{"time":719000,"text":"why there is power in that statement,"},{"time":722000,"text":"I've got to give you the basics of Space 101."},{"time":724000,"text":"And the first thing is everything you do in space you pay by the kilogram."},{"time":732000,"text":"Anybody drink one of these here this week?"},{"time":735000,"text":"You'd pay 10,000 dollars for that in orbit."},{"time":739000,"text":"That's more than you pay for TED,"},{"time":741000,"text":"if Google dropped their sponsorship."},{"time":743000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":746000,"text":"The second is more than 90 percent of the weight of a vehicle is in propellant."},{"time":751000,"text":"Thus, every time you'd want to do anything in space,"},{"time":755000,"text":"you are literally blowing away enormous sums of money"},{"time":759000,"text":"every time you hit the accelerator."},{"time":761000,"text":"Not even the guys at Tesla can fight that physics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"So, what if you could get your gas at a 10th the price?"},{"time":770000,"text":"There is a place where you can."},{"time":773000,"text":"In fact, you can get it better -- you can get it at 14 times lower"},{"time":776000,"text":"if you can find propellant on the moon."},{"time":779000,"text":"There is a little-known mission that was launched"},{"time":781000,"text":"by the Pentagon, 13 years ago now, called Clementine."},{"time":785000,"text":"And the most amazing thing that came out of that mission"},{"time":788000,"text":"was a strong hydrogen signature at Shackleton crater"},{"time":791000,"text":"on the south pole of the moon."},{"time":793000,"text":"That signal was so strong,"},{"time":795000,"text":"it could only have been produced by 10 trillion tons of water"},{"time":799000,"text":"buried in the sediment, collected over millions and billions of years"},{"time":803000,"text":"by the impact of asteroids and comet material."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810000,"text":"If we're going to get that, and make that gas station possible,"},{"time":814000,"text":"we have to figure out ways to move large volumes of payload through space."},{"time":817000,"text":"We can't do that right now."},{"time":819000,"text":"The way you normally build a system right now is you have a tube stack"},{"time":822000,"text":"that has to be launched from the ground,"},{"time":824000,"text":"and resist all kinds of aerodynamic forces."},{"time":826000,"text":"We have to beat that."},{"time":828000,"text":"We can do it because in space there are no aerodynamics."},{"time":831000,"text":"We can go and use inflatable systems for almost everything."},{"time":835000,"text":"This is an idea that, again, came out of Livermore back in 1989,"},{"time":839000,"text":"with Dr. Lowell Wood's group."},{"time":841000,"text":"And we can extend that now to just about everything."},{"time":845000,"text":"Bob Bigelow currently has a test article in the orbit."},{"time":847000,"text":"We can go much further."},{"time":848000,"text":"We can build space tugs, orbiting platforms for holding cryogens and water."},{"time":853000,"text":"There's another thing."},{"time":855000,"text":"When you're coming back from the moon,"},{"time":857000,"text":"you have to deal with orbital mechanics."},{"time":859000,"text":"It says you're moving 10,000 feet per second faster"},{"time":861000,"text":"than you really want to be to get back to your gas station."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"You got two choices."},{"time":866000,"text":"You can burn rocket fuel to get there, or you can do something really incredible."},{"time":870000,"text":"You can dive into the stratosphere,"},{"time":872000,"text":"and precisely dissipate that velocity, and come back out to the space station."},{"time":876000,"text":"It has never been done."},{"time":877000,"text":"It's risky and it's going to be one hell of a ride --"},{"time":881000,"text":"better than Disney."},{"time":883000,"text":"The traditional approach to space exploration"},{"time":885000,"text":"has been that you carry all the fuel you need"},{"time":887000,"text":"to get everybody back in case of an emergency."},{"time":889000,"text":"If you try to do that for the moon,"},{"time":891000,"text":"you're going to burn a billion dollars in fuel alone sending a crew out there."},{"time":895000,"text":"But if you send a mining team there,"},{"time":897000,"text":"without the return propellant, first --"},{"time":899000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":904000,"text":"Did any of you guys hear the story of Cortez?"},{"time":908000,"text":"This is not like that. I'm much more like Scotty."},{"time":910000,"text":"I like this equipment, you know, and I really value it"},{"time":913000,"text":"so we're not going to burn the gear."},{"time":915000,"text":"But, if you were truly bold you could get it there, manufacture it,"},{"time":919000,"text":"and it would be the most dramatic demonstration"},{"time":921000,"text":"that you could do something worthwhile off this planet"},{"time":923000,"text":"that has ever been done."},{"time":925000,"text":"There's a myth that you can't do anything in space"},{"time":928000,"text":"for less than a trillion dollars and 20 years."},{"time":932000,"text":"That's not true."},{"time":933000,"text":"In seven years, we could pull off"},{"time":935000,"text":"an industrial mission to Shackleton and demonstrate"},{"time":937000,"text":"that you could provide commercial reality out of this in low-earth orbit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942000,"text":"We're living in one of the most exciting times in history."},{"time":945000,"text":"We're at a magical confluence where private wealth"},{"time":947000,"text":"and imagination are driving the demand for access to space."},{"time":951000,"text":"The orbital refueling stations I've just described"},{"time":954000,"text":"could create an entirely new industry and provide the final key"},{"time":957000,"text":"for opening space to the general exploration."},{"time":961000,"text":"To bust the paradigm a radically different approach is needed."},{"time":965000,"text":"We can do it by jump-starting with an industrial"},{"time":967000,"text":"Lewis and Clark expedition to Shackleton crater,"},{"time":970000,"text":"to mine the moon for resources, and demonstrate"},{"time":972000,"text":"they can form the basis for a profitable business on orbit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976000,"text":"Talk about space always seems to be hung on ambiguities"},{"time":979000,"text":"of purpose and timing."},{"time":981000,"text":"I would like to close here by putting a stake in the sand at TED."},{"time":986000,"text":"I intend to lead that expedition."},{"time":988000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":996000,"text":"It can be done in seven years with the right backing."},{"time":999000,"text":"Those who join me in making it happen will become a part of history"},{"time":1003000,"text":"and join other bold individuals from time past"},{"time":1005000,"text":"who, had they been here today, would have heartily approved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1010000,"text":"There was once a time when people did bold things to open the frontier."},{"time":1015000,"text":"We have collectively forgotten that lesson."},{"time":1020000,"text":"Now we're at a time when boldness is required to move forward."},{"time":1026000,"text":"100 years after Sir Ernest Shackleton wrote these words,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"I intend to plant an industrial flag on the moon"},{"time":1032000,"text":"and complete the final piece"},{"time":1035000,"text":"that will open the space frontier, in our time, for all of us."},{"time":1039000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1040000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}